commit.message:
Better deal with older version of sphinx

while still allowing docs to build with newer versions

fix doc build with nested sphinx function

`sphinx.main` didn't exist on my sphinx 2.1.0 (Python 3.7.3), but this does (and it built just fine)

This should fix #33.
Initialize username to NULL for server state
Mention we dropped 2.6 and 3.3 in the changelog

Use PyCapsule everywhere

And name our capsules.

Resolves #29
Upgrade Python syntax with pyupgrade https://github.com/asottile/pyupgrade
Drop support for EOL Python 2.6 and 3.3

Username -> UserName

This is a backward breaking change to match ccs-pykerberos.

Resolves #25

Remove mechoid from the server side

And remove the last vestiges of channel bindings from the server side
step function.
Tabs -> spaces to match everything else
Remove channel bindings on the server side

Resolved issues in pull request

Remove "principal", "gssflags", "user", "domain" and "password"
parameters. Remove flags since PyKerberos sets them to NULL.
extra link args for building with mingw
add missing definition of SecPkgContext_Bindings for mingw builds
